<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700 Models - RADIATOR AND COMPONENT REMOVAL -
        RADIATOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>RADIATOR</title>
        <para>Prior to removing the radiator, the radiator shroud and fan assembly must be removed.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Beginning at the upper mounting bolts of the radiator / fan shroud assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201035">Figure 35, Item 2</hotlnk>), loosen and remove the shroud attachment bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201035" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Radiator Fan Shroud Remove</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR TOP FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR / FAN SHROUD MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. RADIATOR / FAN SHROUD</callout1>
                <callout1>4. FAN</callout1>
                <callout1>5. RADIATOR COOLANT PIPES</callout1>
                <callout1>6. GATES POWER GRIP SB HEAT SHRINK CLAMP AND HOSE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the shroud bolts removed, place the shroud assembly back and over the fan assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the fan mounting bolts on the fan drive hub. Loosen and remove fan mounting bolts
                from fan drive hub.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove fan from fan drive hub (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201036">Figure 36, Item 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201036" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 36. Remove Fan From Fan Drive Hub</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR TOP FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR SHROUD MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FAN ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>4. FAN DRIVE HUB</callout1>
                <callout1>5. RADIATOR SHROUD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove both fan and radiator shroud from chassis.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the radiator mounting bolts and lock nuts at the each end of the front crossmember
                assembly. Loosen and remove radiator lock nuts from radiator mounting bolts located at the underside of
                the radiator frame (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201038">Figure 38, Item 3</hotlnk>) and front crossmember.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201037" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 37. Crossmember Radiator Mount Bushing and Washer</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR MOUNTING BUSHING AND WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FRAME RAIL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant, lift radiator to remove bolts from mounting bushing and washer located at
                each end of the front crossmember (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201037">Figure 37, Item 2</hotlnk>). Locate the radiator mounting bracket and mounting
                bolt on the underside of the radiator frame (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201038">Figure 38, Items 2 and 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201038" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 38. Radiator Bottom Frame and Mounting Bolt With Bracket</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR BOTTOM FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>2. RADIATOR MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. MOUNTING BOLTS AND LOCK NUTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201038">Figure 38, Item 3</hotlnk>) from mounting bracket. Follow same procedure on
                driver side.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Before lifting the radiator assembly, disconnect the stay rods - one from the radiator on
                the drivers side, the other at the frame from the passengers side.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201039" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/g1201039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 39. Radiator Remove</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant at each end of the radiator assembly, lift the radiator and carry it out
                through drivers side of chassis (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201039">Figure 39</hotlnk>). Locate the radiator on a work bench or on the floor for
                removal of the radiator frame and core.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
